    <h1>Sub-Zero Built-In Refrigerator Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Sub-Zero is the iconic built-in refrigerator category leader — Madison Wisconsin since 1945, privately held by the Bakke family across 80 years of engineering continuity. The 648 Pro built-in column, Classic BI-36/BI-42/BI-48 side-by-side + French-door models, Pro 48 dual-zone flagship, and ID-series integrated refrigerator drawers anchor LA's luxury built-in kitchen category from Bel Air + Beverly Hills custom remodels through Pacific Palisades + Malibu estate installs. Sub-Zero's dual compressor architecture (independent fresh-food + freezer compressor circuits) is unique in residential refrigeration and shapes every service call — which section is warm tells you which compressor failed. Our LA Sub-Zero built-in service covers current-production 7000 Classic Series + all legacy Classic + 648 + Pro 48 + integrated panel-ready generations, with Sub-Zero Madison WI OEM parts distribution typical 3-5 day LA-authorized service lead on common components. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>Madison WI since 1945</b> — Bakke family privately held</li>
      <li><b>Dual compressor system</b> — independent fresh food + freezer circuits</li>
      <li><b>Sub-Zero Group family</b> — Sub-Zero + Wolf + Cove matched kitchen suite</li>
