  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Sub-Zero built-in column + side-by-side + French-door lineup we service</h2>
    <p>Sub-Zero's built-in refrigerator line covers four main architectures, each with distinct service considerations. The <b>648 Pro built-in</b> is the 48-inch pro-style side-by-side flagship with integrated ice + water dispenser — the signature "full-suite anchor" unit in many LA Sub-Zero Group kitchens. The <b>Classic built-in series</b> (BI-36S 36-inch, BI-42SD 42-inch, BI-48SD 48-inch side-by-side + BI-36UFD / BI-42UFD French-door variants) covers the mid-to-large built-in footprint and installs in the majority of custom luxury kitchens across Beverly Hills, Brentwood, and Pasadena established-luxury cohort. The <b>Pro 48</b> (PRO4850) is the 48-inch dual-zone ultra-premium flagship with advanced humidity control + air purification + separate left-right-section architecture; concentrates in Pacific Palisades + Malibu + ultra-luxury estate kitchens. <b>Integrated refrigerator drawers</b> (ID-36R 36-inch refrigerator drawer / ID-36C 36-inch convertible / ID-24R 24-inch) install at kitchen islands, butler's pantries, or secondary-zone locations for luxury prep-station refrigeration.</p>
    <p>The <b>7000 Classic Series</b> launched approximately 2022 as the refresh of the Classic line with refined digital controls, updated front-grille aesthetics, and revised sensor architecture. Service approach is identical to prior Classic generations — same dual compressor system, same vacuum condenser, same door gasket architecture, same Sub-Zero Madison WI parts channel. Legacy Sub-Zero platforms going back through 1990s-2010s remain service-supported; Madison WI parts distribution maintains catalog depth on legacy components with occasional specialty-component substitution when exact OEM is discontinued. Our techs carry common Sub-Zero service parts (NTC sensors, water inlet valves, ice maker modules, standard gaskets, start relays) on dispatch across generations.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Sub-Zero built-in failures our techs see most often</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Refrigerator warm + freezer fine (or vice versa) — dual compressor differential</h3><p>Textbook Sub-Zero failure pattern. Section-specific warming points immediately to the failed compressor circuit. Start relay + capacitor $240–$380 first; compressor replacement $890–$1,400 if relay clears.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Vacuum condenser clogged — "not cooling" pattern</h3><p>#1 maintenance failure. Front-kick-grille condenser accumulates LA dust over 12-24 months → compressor overheats → cooling capacity drops. Deep clean $120–$180; often resolves without parts.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Ice maker not producing — fresh food section location unique</h3><p>Sub-Zero ice makers are in the fresh-food section (not freezer), different from every other brand. Water inlet valve $280–$380, ice maker module $340–$480, temperature sensor $240–$320.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Door gasket compression loss — warm temperatures pattern</h3><p>10-15 year gasket compression loss causes warm temperatures + excessive compressor cycling. Gasket replacement $280–$420 per section; panel-ready models require careful door-panel removal during service.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Error codes on display — modern generation diagnostic</h3><p>Current-generation Sub-Zero (2015+) displays error codes for sensor / fan / compressor / door faults. We decode per specific model before touching components; many error-code calls resolve at sensor or control board level rather than mechanical.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Integrated panel-ready service without finish damage</h3><p>Full-overlay custom panels on 700 Series integrated + 736TCI + ID-drawer units require panel-protection discipline. Service approach documented at intake; interior work accesses most components without removing the external panel.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Sub-Zero Group three-brand family — matched-suite service context</h2>
    <p>Sub-Zero Group Inc. is a privately-held Bakke-family corporation that owns three luxury residential appliance brands: <b>Sub-Zero</b> (refrigeration + wine storage + undercounter + ice), <b>Wolf</b> (ranges + ovens + cooktops + microwaves + warming drawers), and <b>Cove</b> (dishwashers — launched 2017 as an internal Sub-Zero Group product). A fully coordinated Sub-Zero Group kitchen installs all three brands together — Sub-Zero column refrigerator + Wolf pro-range + Cove dishwasher + optional Sub-Zero wine cooler + optional Sub-Zero freezer column — for a unified luxury aesthetic across the kitchen.</p>
    <p>Service coordination across the three brands flows through the same Sub-Zero Group factory-authorized service network + Madison WI parts distribution, which means multi-appliance service visits across the suite can often be scheduled together for efficiency. For households running the full Sub-Zero Group kitchen, we coordinate service windows across Sub-Zero + Wolf + Cove to minimize total service visits. See dedicated combo pages: <a href="/brands/sub-zero-refrigerator-repair/">Sub-Zero refrigerator repair</a> (standard + freestanding scope, covers legacy freestanding) · <a href="/brands/sub-zero-freezer-repair/">Sub-Zero freezer repair</a> (matched-column freezer) · <a href="/brands/sub-zero-wine-cooler-repair/">Sub-Zero wine cooler repair</a> · <a href="/brands/sub-zero-ice-maker-repair/">Sub-Zero ice maker repair</a> · <a href="/brands/wolf-repair/">Wolf repair</a> (cooking) · <a href="/brands/cove-dishwasher-repair/">Cove dishwasher repair</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Integrated panel-ready architecture — service without finish damage</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>700 Series integrated column</h3><p>36" + 30" integrated refrigerator + freezer columns accepting full-overlay custom panels. Deep European-integration standard for luxury custom kitchens.</p></div>
